.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "December 2025" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a command interpreter (shell) that executes commands read from the standard input or from a file. It mimics the basic functionality of the standard \fBsh\fR shell.
.PP
When invoked, \fBsimple_shell\fR prints a prompt \fB($) \fR and waits for the user to type a command. A command line is terminated by a newline.
.SH INVOCATION
.B simple_shell
can be invoked interactively or non-interactively.
.SS Interactive Mode:
.sp
.B $ ./hsh
.br
.B ($) /bin/ls
.br
file1 file2
.br
.B ($)
.SS Non-Interactive Mode:
.sp
.B $ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.br
file1 file2
.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
Upon receiving a command, \fBsimple_shell\fR tokenizes the input into words. The first word is considered the command name and the subsequent words are the arguments.
.PP
1. Checks if the command is a built-in.
.br
2. Checks if the command is an absolute path (e.g., \fB/bin/ls\fR).
.br
3. Searches for the command in the directories listed in the \fBPATH\fR environment variable.
.SH BUILT-INS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on success, or other values on failure.
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Kriaa9 and your_partner_name.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2)
